doc.after: For many years Cheadle Hulme was rural countryside 48 made up of woods open land and farms The local population was made up of farmers and peasants living in small cottages and working the land under the tenancy of the Lord of the Manor 49 Most families kept animals for food grew their own crops 48 and probably bought and sold produce at Stockport market 49 Water was obtained from local wells and ponds and sometimes the Micker Brook 50
